                              News and Information

  Search the NASA News Archives


     * NASA Newsroom - Indexes of press releases, media advisories, press
       kits, status reports, fact sheets, public reports and biographies.
     * Policy for Accrediting Media Representatives
       You must download the free Adobe Acrobat√Ü Reader to view the policy
       document.
     * "There's Space in My Life . . . " a new initiative to make the
       wealth of NASA's information easily accessible to women, men, and
       their families, and to share how aerospace plays a role in our
       lives right here, close to home.
     * Speakers
       Members of the public interested in having a NASA representative
       address their groups can request an appearance by an astronaut or
       by a NASA scientist, engineer or administrative staff member.
       How do I request a NASA Astronaut to appear before my group?
       How do I request a NASA speaker to appear before my group?
       To request an appearance by a NASA scientist, engineer or
       administrative staff member, contact the NASA Center nearest your
       home.
       Requests for appearances by the NASA Administrator should be mailed
       to:
       Mr. Sean O'Keefe
       Administrator
       National Aeronautics and Space Administration
       Washington, DC 20456-0001
